    <text id="s151405T">
        <front>
            <div1 type="summary">
                <p>Confederate General William Loring writes from Staunton in December, 1861, with
                    orders for Colonel William B. Taliaferro.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div1 type="letter">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Col. W. B. TALIAFERRO,<lb/> Cmdg. Brigade:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-12-04">December 4, 1861.</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, Va.,</name> <name type="location">HDQRS. NORTHWEST ARMY,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>COL.:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You will upon receipt of this take your command upon the cars to Strasburg, and
                    there await further orders. I have received instructions from the War Department
                    to this effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully, your obedient servant,</salute>
                    <signed>W. W. LORING,<lb/> Brig.-Gen., Cmdg., &amp;c.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
